Barclays Plc (BARC)  may acquire Spanish
savings bank  Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo (CAM) , or CAM, with
guarantees from the Bank of Spain,  El Confidencial  reported,
citing unidentified people close to the matter.  CAM, which has about 1,000 offices in Spain, would help
Barclays boost its presence in the country, the financial news
website said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
